The paper deals with information exchange in multi-cell multiuser networks, which involves aspects of information theory (cs.IT), networking (cs.NI), and control systems (cs.SY). The use of cooperative MIMO (multiple-input multiple-output) techniques also falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the optimal capacity scaling, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT).
